It has already been reported as an alternative splicing modulator of the HMGCR gene through exon definition.

It has been reported that hnRNP L RNA interactions in human T cells and identify the hnRNP L-dependent splicing regulation of cellular pathways as critical for T cell development and immune function. Another study reported that hnRNP L is the main protein responsible for ESS1-mediated exonic silencing.

gene-description: MeCP2 binds to methylated exonic DNA, shutting down RNA Polymerase II (RNAPII), thus reducing the chance of skipping alternative exons. A functional analysis reveals that genes containing exons regulated by MeCP2 are primarily involved in synaptic functions and mRNA processing. It was also reported that MeCP2 regulated mRNA splicing through interaction with 5hmC and epigenetic changes in histone markers.

Nova1 binds to YCAY-rich elements (where Y represents a pyrimidine) and is a central regulator of alternative neuronal splicing. It was further reported that Nova1 may have an alternative splicing master regulatory role in pancreatic beta cells.

gene-description: It can regulate RNA splicing or metabolism in a specific subset of developing neurons. It binds directly to the YCAY motifs (where Y represents a pyrimidine) in the messenger RNA (mRNA) sequence. Depending on the location of the binding in the mRNA, it can induce exon skipping or exon retention.

gene-description: It plays a role in pre-mRNA splicing and regulation of alternative splicing events. It activates exon skipping of its own pre-mRNA during muscle cell differentiation. This protein binds to intronic polypyrimidine tracts that require pre-mRNA splicing and acts through the ubiquitin-proteasome protein degradation pathway. It can also promote the binding of U2 snRNP to pre-mRNAs. It cooperates with RAVER1 to modulate the alternation between mutually exclusive exons during TPM1 pre-mRNA maturation. Represses MAPT / Tau exon 10 splicing.

gene-name: RNA binding protein with serine rich domain 1
gene-description: Part of the pre- and post-splicing mRNP multiprotein complexes. It is a component of the splicing-dependent mRNP complex, called the exon-exon junction complex (EJC). Increases spliceosome ATP-dependent complex A formation. Involved in constitutive splicing and, in association with SRP54 and TRA2B / SFRS10, in the distinct modulation of alternative splicing in a substrate-dependent manner. Involved in the modulation of BCL2L1/Bcl-X splicing and specifically inhibits the formation of pro-apoptotic isoforms such as Bcl-X(S). Participates in the cleavage of the 3' end of the mRNA.

gene-description: Involved in pre-mRNA splicing as a component of the splicing factor 3b (SF3B) protein complex. SF3B1 is a key component of the U2 snRNP complex; it binds to the adenosine branch point in the early stages of spliceosome assembly and facilitates the formation of the complex responsible for splicing. Sequence-independent binding of the SF3A / SF3B complex upstream of the branch site is essential, it can anchor U2 snRNP to pre-mRNA. It may also be involved in the assembly of the 'E' complex. It also belongs to the U12-dependent minor spliceosome, which is involved in splicing a rare class of nuclear pre-mRNA intron.

gene-description: Required for processing pre-mRNA as a component of the spliceosome. It participates in the second catalytic step of pre-mRNA splicing, when the free hydroxyl group of exon I attacks the 3'-splice site to generate mature mRNA. Necessary to keep exon 1 firmly within the spliceosome and for the correct identification of the AG when more than one possible AG exists in the region of the 3' splicing site.

gene-description: The SMN complex plays a catalytic role in the assembly of small nuclear ribonucleoproteins (snRNPs), the building blocks of the spliceosome. Dissociation by the SMN complex from CLNS1A from the trapped Sm proteins and their transfer to an SMN-Sm complex triggers the assembly of snRNPs from the nucleus and their transport to the nucleus. Ensures the correct splicing of genes containing intron U12 that may be important for the normal development of motor and proprioceptive neurons.

gene-description: A splicing factor specifically required for neural cell differentiation. Necessary to promote the inclusion of neural-specific exon 10 in nPTB / PTBP2, leading to increased expression of neural-specific nPTB / PTBP2. It also promotes the inclusion of exon 16 in DAAM1 in neuron extracts. Activates neural exon inclusion by binding to motifs containing intronic UGCs proximal to suboptimal 3 ′ splice sites. It promotes alternative splicing of REST transcripts by activating the inclusion of an exon to produce the REST isoform (REST4) that lacks critical domains necessary for REST-mediated transcriptional silencing of neuronal target genes.

gene-name: serine and arginine rich splicing factor 1
gene-description: It plays a role in preventing exon skipping, ensuring splicing accuracy and regulating alternate splicing. It interacts with other spliceosomal components, via the RS domains, to form a bridge between the 5' and 3' splice site binding components, U1 snRNP and U2AF. It can stimulate the binding of U1 snRNP to a pre-mRNA containing a 5' splice site. It binds to purine-rich RNA sequences, either the octamer, 5'-RGAAGAAC-3' (r = A or G) or the decamers, AGGACAGAGC / AGGACGAAGC.

gene-name: serine and arginine rich splicing factor 10
gene-description: A splicing factor that in its dephosphorylated form acts as a general repressor of pre-mRNA splicing. It appears to interfere with the recognition of 5' U1 snRNP splice of SNRNP70. Required for splicing repression in M-phase cells and after heat shock. It also acts as a splicing factor that specifically promotes exon skipping during alternate splicing. gene-description: Heterogeneous nuclear ribonucleoprotein (hnRNP) implicated in mRNA processing mechanisms. Component of the CRD-mediated complex that promotes the stability of MYC mRNA. Isoform 1, isoform 2 and isoform 3 are associated in vitro with pre-mRNA, splicing intermediates and mature mRNA protein complexes. Isoform 1 binds to AU-rich sequences of apoB mRNA. It interacts in vitro preferentially with poly(A) and poly(U) RNA sequences.

gene-description: It plays a role as a regulator of holoenzyme transcription of RNA polymerase II (Pol II). It plays a role as an alternative global pre-mRNA splicing modulator, regulating the biogenesis of the small nuclear ribonucleoprotein U2 (snRNP). It binds to the 3'-UTR of TNFA mRNA.

gene-description: ELAV-like 3 is a neuron-specific RNA-binding protein that contains three RNP-like RNA recognition motifs. It binds to AU-rich element (ARE) sequences of target mRNAs, including VEGF mRNA.

gene-description: An RNA binding protein that is involved in the post-transcriptional regulation of mRNAs. It binds to AU rich element (ARE) sequences in the 3' untranslated region (UTR) of target mRNAs, including GAP43, VEGF, FOS, CDKN1A and ACHE mRNA. By binding to 3'UTR mRNA, it decreases mRNA deadenylation. it also binds to the polyadenylated tail (poly(A)) in the 3'UTR of the mRNA, thus increasing its affinity for mRNA binding. It acts as a stabilizing factor by binding to NOVA1 3'UTR mRNA, thus increasing its translation and enhancing its functional activity in neuron-specific splicing. It can regulate alternative splicing of CALCA pre-mRNA to calcitonin and calcitonin gene-related peptide 1 (CGRP) by competing with the splicing regulator TIAR for binding to U-rich intronic sequences of CALCA pre-mRNA.

gene-description: RNA binding protein that binds to the 3'-UTR region of mRNAs and increases their stability. It binds to poly-U elements and AU-rich elements (AREs) in the 3'-UTR of target mRNAs. With ZNF385A, it binds the 3'-UTR of p53 / TP53 mRNA to control its CDKN2A-induced nuclear export. Therefore, it can regulate the expression of p53 / TP53 and mediate in part the antiproliferative activity of CDKN2A. It can also bind CCNB1 mRNA with ZNF385A.

gene-description: The KHSRP gene encodes a multifunctional RNA-binding protein implicated in a variety of cellular processes, including transcription, alternative pre-mRNA splicing, and Mrna localization. It mediates exon inclusion in transcripts that are subject to tissue-specific alternative splicing. Also involved in the degradation of inherently unstable mRNAs that contain AU-rich elements (AREs) in their 3'-UTR, possibly recruiting degradation machinery for ARE-containing mRNAs.

gene-name: splicing factor proline and glutamine rich
gene-description: Essential pre-mRNA splicing factor needed in early spliceosome formation and for catalytic splicing of step II, probably as a heteromer with NONO. It binds to pre-mRNA in the spliceosome C complex and specifically binds to intronic polypyrimidine tracts. It interacts with U5 snRNA, probably binding to a purine-rich sequence located on the 3' side of the U5 snRNA 1b stem. It may be involved in a process of splicing and polyadenylation coupled to pre-mRNA as a component of a free complex of snRNP with SNRPA / U1A. It has been reported that e plays an important role in maintaining intron integrity, ensuring accurate splicing of long introns.

gene-description: An RNA-binding protein that acts as a regulator of alternative pre-mRNA splicing. Involved in apoptotic cell death by regulating the expression of the apoptotic factor BCL2L1 isoform. Modulates the ratio of pro-apoptotic BCL2L1 isoform S to anti-apoptotic BCL2L1 isoform L mRNA expression by stimulating 5'-splice (5'-ss) site selection. Its association with LUC7L3 promotes U1 snRNP binding to a weak 5' ss in a 5'-CGGGCA-3' dependent manner. It binds to the 5'-CGGGCA-3' RNA sequence of the exonic splicing enhancer located in exon 2 of the BCL2L1 pre-mRNA.

gene-description: Modulates alternate 5' splice location and exon selection. Activates exon skipping of PTB pre-mRNA during muscle cell differentiation. It antagonizes the activity of the splicing factor PTBP1 to modulate the muscle cell-specific exon selection of alpha-tropomyosin. It binds to the intronic pyrimidine-rich sequence of TPM1 and MAPT pre-mRNAs. RBM4 plays an important role in the exchange of PKM isoforms and in the change in mitochondrial energy production during neuronal differentiation. RBM4 is involved in alternative splicing of exon 10 of tau.

gene-description: Component of the spliceosome complex A. Regulates alternative splicing of various mRNAs. It can modulate splice site pairing after recruiting the U1 and U2 snRNPs to the 5' and 3' intron splice sites. It can up- and down-regulate apoptosis by regulating the alternative splicing of several genes involved in this process, including FAS and CASP2/caspase-2. In the case of FAS, it promotes the exclusion of exon 6, thus producing a soluble form of FAS that inhibits apoptosis. In the case of CASP2/caspase-2, it promotes the exclusion of exon 9, thus producing a catalytically active form of CASP2/Caspase-2 that induces apoptosis.

gene-name: KH RNA binding domain containing, signal transduction associated 1
gene-description: An RNA binding protein that plays a role in regulating alternative splicing and influences mRNA splice site selection and exon inclusion. It binds to RNA containing 5'-[AU]UAA-3' as a bipartite motif spaced by more than 15 nucleotides. Alloy poly(A). It can regulate alternative CD44 splicing in a Ras-dependent manner. In cooperation with HNRNPA1 it modulates alternative splicing of BCL2L1 promoting splicing towards the Bcl-X (S) and SMN1 isoform. It can regulate the alternative splicing of NRXN1 and NRXN3 in the laminin G-like domain 6 containing the evolutionary conserved neurexin alternative splicing segment 4 (AS4) involved in selective targeting of neurexin to postsynaptic partners. In a neuronal activity-dependent manner, it cooperates synergistically with KHDRBS2/SLIM-1 in the regulation of exon skipping NRXN1 in AS4. The cooperation with KHDRBS2 / SLIM-1 is antagonistic to the regulation of alternative NXRN3 splicing in AS4.

gene-description: Part of the pre- and post-splicing mRNP multiprotein complexes. Involved in various pre-mRNA processing events. Promotes constitutive and exonic splicing enhancer (ESE) - binding-dependent splicing activation between sequence-specific factors (SR family proteins, SFRS4, SFRS5 and TRA2B / SFRS10) and basal snRNP (SNRP70 and SNRPA1) of the spliceosome. It stimulates cleavage of the 3' end of mRNA, independent of the formation of an exon junction complex. Binds pre-mRNA and spliced ​​mRNA ​​20-25 nt upstream of the exon-exon junctions.

gene-name: serine and arginine rich splicing factor 6
gene-description: It plays a role in constitutive splicing and modulates the selection of alternative splicing sites. Plays a role in MAPT / Tau exon 10 alternative splicing. It binds to alternative exons of TNC pre-mRNA and promotes alternatively spliced ​​TNC expression. It plays a role in wound healing and in regulating keratinocyte differentiation and proliferation through its role in alternative splicing. It has been reported that SRSF6 is able to trigger the activation of DDR pathways via alternative splicing regulation to influence cancer progression.

gene-description: It acts predominantly as an RNA-binding protein: it binds preferentially to the 5'-[CU] CUGCG-3' RNA motif and specifically recognizes mRNA transcripts modified by C5-methylcytosine (m5C). Also involved in regulation of pre-mRNA alternative splicing: it binds to splice sites in pre-mRNA and regulates splice site selection. YB-1 together with hnRNP L and hnRNP C have been reported to regulate the alternative skipping of exon 10 of the human MUSK gene. YB-1 binds to the A/C-rich exon enhancer element in the CD44 gene and thus directs alternative splicing.

gene-name: SWI/SNF related, matrix associated, actin dependent regulator of chromatin, subfamily a, member 1
gene-description: SWI / SNF proteins can act as regulators and alternative splicing, their catalytic subunit Brm favors the inclusion of variant exons in the mRNA of several genes, including E-cadherin, BIM, cyclin D1 and CD44. It associates several components of the spliceosome such as the U1 and U5 snRNAs and with the PRP6 and Sam68 proteins, suggesting a role in the recruitment of the splicing machinery.

gene-description: An RNA-binding protein involved in the regulation of various post-transcriptional events. Involved in alternative pre-mRNA splicing, translation and mRNA stability. It mediates exon inclusion and/or exclusion in pre-mRNA that are subject to alternative tissue-specific and developmentally regulated splicing. It specifically activates the inclusion of exon 5 of TNNT2 cardiac isoforms during heart remodeling in the juvenile-to-adult transition. It binds to the intronic muscle-specific splicing enhancer (MSE) sites that flank alternate exon 5 of the TNNT2 pre-mRNA. It acts as an activator and repressor of a pair of co-regulated exons: it promotes the inclusion of the smooth muscle (SM) exon, but the exclusion of the non-muscle (NM) exon in actinin pre-mRNAs. Activates the inclusion of SM exon 5 antagonizing the repressive effect of PTB. Promotes the exclusion of exon 11 from the INSR pre-mRNA. It inhibits, along with HNRNPH1, the inclusion of exon 11 of the insulin receptor (IR) pre-mRNA in the myoblast.

gene-description: An RNA-binding protein implicated in the regulation of various post-transcriptional events. Involved in alternative pre-mRNA splicing, translation and mRNA stability. It mediates exon inclusion and/or exclusion in pre-mRNA that are subject to alternative tissue-specific and developmentally regulated splicing. It specifically activates the inclusion of TNNT2 exon 5 in embryonic, but not adult, skeletal muscle. It binds to the intronic muscle-specific splicing enhancer (MSE) sites that flank alternate exon 5 TNNT2. Activates the inclusion of exon 5 of TNNT2, antagonizing the repressive effect of PTB. gene-description: Involved in pre-mRNA splicing as a component of the splicing factor SF3B complex, a constituent of the spliceosome. SF3B complex is required for 'A' complex assembly formed by the stable binding of U2 snRNP to the branchpoint sequence (BPS) in pre-mRNA. Sequence independent binding of SF3A/SF3B complex upstream of the branch site is essential, it may anchor U2 snRNP to the pre-mRNA. May also be involved in the assembly of the 'E' complex. Belongs also to the minor U12-dependent spliceosome, which is involved in the splicing of rare class of nuclear pre-mRNA intron.
spliceosomal-class: E, A B Complex, and U2 snRNA

gene-description: Involved in pre-mRNA splicing as a component of the splicing factor SF3B complex. SF3B complex is required for 'A' complex assembly formed by the stable binding of U2 snRNP to the branchpoint sequence (BPS) in pre-mRNA. Directly contacts the pre-mRNA branch site adenosine for the first catalytic step of splicing. Enters the spliceosome and associates with the pre-mRNA branch site as part of the 17S U2 or, in the case of the minor spliceosome, as part of the 18S U11/U12 snRNP complex, and thus may facilitate the interaction of these snRNP with the branch sites of U2 and U12 respectively.

gene-description: Component of the cap-binding complex (CBC), which binds cotranscriptionally to the 5'-cap of pre-mRNAs and is involved in various processes such as pre-mRNA splicing, translation regulation, nonsense-mediated mRNA decay, RNA-mediated gene silencing (RNAi) by microRNAs (miRNAs) and mRNA export. The CBC complex enhances NMD in mRNAs containing at least one exon-junction complex (EJC) via its interaction with UPF1, promoting the interaction between UPF1 and UPF2.

gene-description: Ubiquitin-protein ligase which is a core component of several complexes mainly involved pre-mRNA splicing and DNA repair. Required for pre-mRNA splicing as component of the spliceosome. Core component of the PRP19C/Prp19 complex/NTC/Nineteen complex which is part of the spliceosome and participates in its assembly, its remodeling and is required for its activity. During assembly of the spliceosome, mediates 'Lys-63'-linked polyubiquitination of the U4 spliceosomal protein PRPF3. Ubiquitination of PRPF3 allows its recognition by the U5 component PRPF8 and stabilizes the U4/U5/U6 tri-snRNP spliceosomal complex. ecruited to RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain (CTD) and the pre-mRNA, it may also couple the transcriptional and spliceosomal machineries.

Plays a role in stabilizing the structure of the spliceosome catalytic core and docking of the branch helix into the active site, producing 5'-exon and lariat intron-3'-intermediates.

gene-description: Involved in pre-mRNA splicing as component of the spliceosome. Core component of the splicing-dependent multiprotein exon junction complex (EJC) deposited at splice junctions on mRNAs. The EJC is a dynamic structure consisting of core proteins and several peripheral nuclear and cytoplasmic associated factors that join the complex only transiently either during EJC assembly or during subsequent mRNA metabolism. The EJC marks the position of the exon-exon junction in the mature mRNA for the gene expression machinery and the core components remain bound to spliced mRNAs throughout all stages of mRNA metabolism thereby influencing downstream processes including nuclear mRNA export, subcellular mRNA localization, translation efficiency and nonsense-mediated mRNA decay.

The EJC marks the position of the exon-exon junction in the mature mRNA for the gene expression machinery and the core components remain bound to spliced mRNAs throughout all stages of mRNA metabolism thereby influencing downstream processes including nuclear mRNA export, subcellular mRNA localization, translation efficiency and nonsense-mediated mRNA decay (NMD).

gene-description: Required for pre-mRNA splicing as component of the spliceosome. Core component of the splicing-dependent multiprotein exon junction complex (EJC) deposited at splice junctions on mRNAs. The EJC is a dynamic structure consisting of core proteins and several peripheral nuclear and cytoplasmic associated factors that join the complex only transiently either during EJC assembly or during subsequent mRNA metabolism. The EJC marks the position of the exon-exon junction in the mature mRNA for the gene expression machinery and the core components remain bound to spliced mRNAs throughout all stages of mRNA metabolism thereby influencing downstream processes including nuclear mRNA export, subcellular mRNA localization, translation efficiency and nonsense-mediated mRNA decay (NMD). Involved in the splicing modulation of BCL2L1/Bcl-X (and probably other apoptotic genes); specifically inhibits formation of proapoptotic isoforms such as Bcl-X(S); the function is different from the established EJC assembly.

gene-description: Required for pre-mRNA splicing as component of the spliceosome. Core component of the splicing-dependent multiprotein exon junction complex (EJC) deposited at splice junctions on mRNAs. The EJC is a dynamic structure consisting of core proteins and several peripheral nuclear and cytoplasmic associated factors that join the complex only transiently either during EJC assembly or during subsequent mRNA metabolism. The EJC marks the position of the exon-exon junction in the mature mRNA for the gene expression machinery and the core components remain bound to spliced mRNAs throughout all stages of mRNA metabolism thereby influencing downstream processes including nuclear mRNA export, subcellular mRNA localization, translation efficiency and nonsense-mediated mRNA decay (NMD). Binds spliced mRNA in sequence-independent manner, 20-24 nucleotides upstream of mRNA exon-exon junctions.

gene-description: Pre-mRNA processing factor involved in disassembly of spliceosomes after the release of mature mRNA. gene-description: Component of the spliceosomal U1 snRNP, which is essential for recognition of the pre-mRNA 5' splice-site and the subsequent assembly of the spliceosome. SNRPC/U1-C is directly involved in initial 5' splice-site recognition for both constitutive and regulated alternative splicing. The interaction with the 5' splice-site seems to precede base-pairing between the pre-mRNA and the U1 snRNA. Stimulates commitment or early (E) complex formation by stabilizing the base pairing of the 5' end of the U1 snRNA and the 5' splice-site region.
